One person has died following a shooting incident in Margate
on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast on Wednesday. According to KwaZulu Private Ambulance Service spokesperson,
Craig Botha, when emergency services arrived at the scene, they found that two
people in a vehicle had been shot. One of them sustained minor injuries and was treated at the
scene and the other was already dead. “The circumstances of the shooting are being investigated by
the authorities,” he said.